{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_30","type":"agent_message","text":"Human intervention needed\n\nThe automated job failed for `org.apache.maven.doxia:doxia-module-apt:1.1`. Preserved work is available here: https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/tree/ai%2Fvjovanov%2Fhuman-intervention%2Fissue-7030-fails-javac-compile-org.apache.maven.doxia-doxia-module-apt-1.1-74fdb646\n\nThe run initially failed in javac because the copied `1.0` test no longer matched the `1.1` API: `AptSink(Writer)` is protected, and `AptSink.encodeFragment(String)` / `AptSink.encodeURL(String)` are not present in `1.1` (`human-intervention-logs/org.apache.maven.doxia:doxia-module-apt:1.1/gradle-test/gradle-test-2026-06-07T08-16-00-174705Z.log`). After that was adjusted, the next run still failed because two assertions expected nested `paragraph` events inside list/numbered-list items that `1.1` does not emit (`parserEmitsStructuredEventsForRichAptDocument()` and `parserEmitsNestedNumberedListsWithExplicitNumberingStyles()` in `human-intervention-logs/org.apache.maven.doxia:doxia-module-apt:1.1/gradle-test/gradle-test-2026-06-07T08-17-53-838636Z.log`).\n\nLater reruns passed cleanly, including `nativeTest` and the top-level Gradle `:test` task (`human-intervention-logs/org.apache.maven.doxia:doxia-module-apt:1.1/gradle-test/gradle-test-2026-06-07T08-18-43-392209Z.log`, `...08-19-34-051650Z.log`, `...08-19-50-311543Z.log`, `...08-20-06-556432Z.log`). The most likely failing stage is therefore post-test automation/reporting rather than the library test itself: `stats/org.apache.maven.doxia/doxia-module-apt/1.1/execution-metrics.json` still records `\"status\": \"failure\"`, `\"generated_loc\": 0`, and `\"artifacts\": {\"test_file\": \"None\", \"metadata_file\": \"None\"}` even though commit `763169c5209e1b1234210652fbd0236bc732a7e0` on the preserved branch contains a passing candidate.\n\nNext steps:\n- Inspect or cherry-pick commit `763169c5209e1b1234210652fbd0236bc732a7e0` from the preserved branch; it contains the test and metadata updates that passed.\n- Re-run `./gradlew test -Pcoordinates=org.apache.maven.doxia:doxia-module-apt:1.1` to confirm the passing candidate locally.\n- Check the automation/reporting path that writes `stats/org.apache.maven.doxia/doxia-module-apt/1.1/execution-metrics.json`, because the recorded failure status does not match the later successful Gradle runs."}}
